76561198001790442,Recommended,314520,18979761,"Posted: 9 November, 2015",all,Sistermatic,"This is not going to show as an ""Early Access review"" but as far as I'm concerned it should be. DTG pushed the release on this (Nov 2), perhaps to try and counter Fishing Planet.It was a mistake because the bugs and problems with this are numerous.Some of the glaringly obvious:-- Fish that SLIDE sideways, they don't swim at all. Sure, their tails wag but that's the model, not the AI. They almost teleport they move so fast sometimes. Even the biggest fish around the 40kg mark, bounce and slide around like a Smartie in a blender. I've written script for fish and rotating them ""naturally"" is a pretty simple task. Adding proper inertia and momentum is a little trickier but certainly doable too.- The casting is not bad (with practise) but a 50m cast, to the opposite side of a lake, which looks to be 150-200m away, is up on the bank. 2 winds of the reel and you're back in the middle of the lake at 30m or so. In some cases you can't even see where your gear is until you bring it back to under 30m.- Reel winding is shocking. A 5:1 reel, with zero tension, should be bringing in close to a metre of line per turn. You can literally turn the handle 50 times and get back a metre of line. I made this observation in the forums and was told it's an ""audio"" problem because I mentioned I should at least be hearing the clutch slipping. Did they answer about not being able to wind in with zero tension or that my reel acts like it's  1:25 ratio?  Not even mentioned.- Fish snap off, for no reason, in some places on some maps. Can't even be bothered reporting it.- The fish ""fight"" is only really differentiated by time. A BIG fish in RL can and will run for 10's of metres non-stop, sheer power. Smaller fish dart and dance. Some of these 40kg monsters swim like a Goldfish and you get frustratingly stuck with a bouncing yo-yo fish, 7m out and 5m deep, going nowhere. Some smaller fish, where your breaking strain is 3 times that of fish, simply ""lock up"" 10m out and just pull against the line. You cannot wind them in, you have to pump and wind like it's a 10kg carp.- 15lb Touchdown line is borked. Unlimited drag. Max it to 100% and skulldrag your fish straight in. I mentioned this is a pretty serious exploit because XP and TP (the currency) is linked to catches. There are also live tournaments against real players and anyone NOT fishing 15lb will lose - obviously. Answer from devs. ""It's up to you if you use it or not"".- Tournament scores do not update in RT, in some cases not at all.- ""Boss"" fish are able to be caught one after another. I caught 5 in a row, from the same location, using the same gear, line, bait. everything.- My favourite. You can catch a ""Boss"" fish (all independently named) on Rod #1 and while you're taking it off the hook, Rod #2 goes off and presto..... same Boss fish. I've caught 3 in a row on this, others have caught the same Boss 5 times in a row.- FPS is capped at 30fps. Yes folks. UE4 engine, PC game, CAPPED at 30fps.- AMD users are suffering all kinds of glitching, gamma, flickering and crashes. Devs say it's AMD and/or Epic (UE4). Anyone who playes the multitude of UE4 games out there (Ark is one of the most popular) knows that AMD cards are NOT suffering this across the board.- VERY short gameplay. In 40 hours, much of it playing the broken tournaments, I am nearly maxed out and own almost everything.- The gear. Some of it is so similar (or lacking in gameplay neccessity) that it makes accumulation pointless. BUT, you need to buy item #1 to be able to buy item #2 so... accumulate you do.Look. I've had enough of this, I've annoyed myself, sounding all whiney and sooky. I could go on but just the attitudes of devs to problems you officially document is pretty poor. A whole lot of pseudo-surprise, ""we'll look into it"", ""our testing didn't do that""  etc... all the while telling you they're working on more content, and given it's Dovetail Games, it'll be mostly DLC.For now. IF it's on special it might be worth a look because they MAY address these issues. $20 for 40 hours is probably not too bad so I'll not complain too much more.IF this had been an Early Access title my review would be completely different and my tolerance for errors would be much, much higher. But when you release broken titles... Shame.5/10It get's an up.... Just. It is fishing, it's kinda relaxing and looks reasonable. It will be good for awhile but you'll run out of fun very quickly."
