76561197980007031,Recommended,314520,16745281,"Posted: 27 June, 2015",all,Dorenno,"Are you an angler? If yes, this is your game. If I have to compare this game with the others from the past, this work is the most definitive masterpiece from all times. It aims for the relaxing side of lakeside amusement. No need to reel in to catch  your bass or pike, just use your wits to select your most effective rig, choose your most attracting bait, make a precise throw and wait for the bite. If everything's in harmony, you don't have to wait too long. The bite alarm will go off, and there you go... The fish fights, kicks, struggles as long as her energy keeps her moving. Is she big? Well mate, she will make you sweat because the rod behaviour and the the line tension are as realistic as in real life. It's not a rare thing, when you fight with the fish for 20 or 30 minutes. Keep the tension downs for a sec and off she goes... Your fish swims away like a lightening, and you stare at your empty hook thinking: ""How's that possible?"" On the other hand. If you're the better one: your catch tires out, lying exhausted on top of the water , you're still have to use your net to catch you prey. One wrong move, and the sleeping beauty awakes and off the hook... In short terms: This game is awesome, even, if it's in early acces stage. I just can't do anything else, only to recommend it!"
